<font color="#FF0000">BROTHERS, BONDED BY NEED</font><br>
<tt>Sun Nov 16 10:40:07 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Anne,<br><br>
The position you hold because of the honor we bestow is not taken lightly.  As we or any Marine would say, you hold your position because of your actions so well represented by your words.<br><br>
Know you are here because you are one of us.  Accepted as you are without reservation.  It is this unconditional trust we give that makes us what we are.<br><br>
Honor, integrity, and truth is the strength we have.  We bond because we are of a common thread.  We love our country, our brothers, and those we sought to defend without regard to their views.<br><br>
It is our resolve to refuse to accept condemnation or denial of our place in history that brings us to this site.<br><br>
We bond again to protect our brothers as we always have.  This group brings a peace to me that I never knew I lost.
<p><code>--   (SW) </code><p>


